				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">From new developer Sam Hayne at the Sony forums:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">...the [Prowler] has, if fully manned, 2x the overall damage [of the Vanguard] per second if all guns are hitting.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
So when Ash points out that not only is his statement wrong but goes on to talk about the crappiness of the Prowler in general with his statistics and computations (which are 95% correct), Sam has to reiterate:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Your damage numbers are way off.  Again, the Prowler is OVER 2 TIMES the damage output over time (if fully manned) than a Vanguard.  Change your numbers to be the Prowler's doing 1000 damage a second vs. the Vanguard's 450 damage per second and you are close to what is really going on.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I'm sure he intended to say that his damage/second stats in this case were meant over two seconds instead of one, but in either situation, he's simply mistaken.
<br />

<br />
Ironically, Sam seems to understand on some level that the Prowler's secondary gun simply isn't manpower-efficient:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">And, if the TR want to roll 4 prowlers without chaingunners and a skyguard to keep the air off, how does that work out?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Ding ding ding.</span>  This is what we've been doing for over six months.  But the fact that we're trying to make the best possible use of our equipment doesn't make the Prowler any less of a hunk of junk compared to its empire equivalents.  Oh, and the precise answer to his question (how it would work out leaving Prowler machine gun spots empty) is, "Way better than filling them ever could."  The worse-than-useless gun spot is just a glaring example of developer lameness.
<br />
____________________________________________________
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I guess I'm just concerned about the direction the game is headed in.  Like someone said in the thread, how can the devs hope to balance the game if they don't completely understand what's going on in it?  The recent developments of the horrifically inefficient Raider and Sam's strange and incorrect Prowler apologetics haven't boosted my confidence as a TR player.
<br />

<br />
Full thread at:
<br />
<a href="http://psforums.station.sony.com/ps/board/message?board.id=psdiscussion&amp;message.id=331398" target="_blank">http://psforums.station.sony.com/ps/board/message?board.id=psdiscussion&amp;message.id=331398</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
