<br />
I agree wholeheartedly, but I think there are drawbacks too, the main one in my eyes being the downtime caused by messing around with random pickup gunners.  Unless there are a lot of people just sitting around at the vehicle pad, I usually don't see anyone willing to get in the machine gun of my Prowler in any reasonable amount of time.  You can chase people around spamming "We need a gunner," but I rarely bother to... it just doesn't seem worth the effort.  I want to be getting back to the battlefront as fast as I can.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>oaksilencer wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">it costs no certs to gun, there is no timer to gun.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
